		"description": "<p>While the construction of this cup is superlative, the magnificence of its craftsmanship is turned wicked by the grotesque gold-crowned humanoid skull that makes up its bowl. When you use this spellcasting focus to consume Supply during a long rest, you gain a 1d8 expertise die on your next Arcana or Religion check. After making this check, you make a Charisma saving throw (DC 1 + 1 per previous use of this property) or gain the Evil trait (making you radiate an aura of Evil).</p><p>In addition, once per day you can place the blood of a creature that has died within the last hour into the goblet and drink from it. You instantly experi- ence the last 10 minutes of the creature&rsquo;s life through its senses, and you have disadvantage on your next Charisma saving throw against Nemirtvi&rsquo;s skull goblet.</p>",
